Here's how to implement all three in your `EditProductPage`:

**XAML — Custom "Cancel" back button:**

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="MyApp.EditProductPage"
             Title="Edit Product">

    <Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
        <BackButtonBehavior
            TextOverride="Cancel"
            Command="{Binding NavigateBackCommand}" />
    </Shell.BackButtonBehavior>

    <!-- your form here -->
</ContentPage>
```

**Code-behind / ViewModel — Intercept and confirm:**

```csharp
// In your ViewModel (or code-behind)
public bool HasUnsavedChanges { get; set; }

public ICommand NavigateBackCommand { get; }

public EditProductViewModel()
{
    NavigateBackCommand = new AsyncRelayCommand(OnNavigateBackAsync);
}

private async Task OnNavigateBackAsync()
{
    if (HasUnsavedChanges)
    {
        bool leave = await Shell.Current.DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "You have unsaved changes. Discard and go back?",
            "Discard", "Stay");

        if (!leave) return;           // cancel navigation
    }

    await Shell.Current.GoBackAsync();
}
```

**Android hardware back button** — override in the page code-behind, since `BackButtonBehavior.Command` only covers the Shell navbar button:

```csharp
// EditProductPage.xaml.cs
protected override bool OnBackButtonPressed()
{
    // Fire-and-forget the async confirmation
    Dispatcher.Dispatch(async () =>
    {
        if (ViewModel.HasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            bool leave = await DisplayAlert(
                "Unsaved Changes",
                "You have unsaved changes. Discard and go back?",
                "Discard", "Stay");

            if (!leave) return;
        }

        await Shell.Current.GoBackAsync();
    });

    return true;  // true = we handled it, suppress default back
}
```

**Key points:**

| Mechanism | What it covers |
|---|---|
| `BackButtonBehavior.Command` | Shell navbar back button (all platforms) |
| `OnBackButtonPressed()` override | Android hardware/gesture back |
| Return `true` from `OnBackButtonPressed` | Cancels default navigation |

Both paths funnel through the same confirmation logic and call `GoBackAsync()` only if the user confirms.
